such a bad thing for people to auction their stuff.  I for one am not &quot;uber&quot; and am not looking for 30k items, but I do have several alts that I'm always shopping for, and since they are alts I don't always know what the good gear is for them, and thus don't know what to search for.  When people auction it gives me the chance to see items that would be decent for my alts but that I wouldn't have otherwise known about.  I'm also always looking for a bargain, and although there are many times that I've seen people auction something for the lowest price, and I then searched the bazaar and found it sold for less, there have also been a few times where the person really did have a great deal on an item that I was interested in, and I took it.  Had they not auctioned it I wouldn't have found it.  In short, I don't think the bazaar has to be a place where people have to shut up and just offer their wares through /trader, it's very fitting with the role-playing atmosphere for the traders to be very vocal in order to bring prospective customers to their shop.  Can you tell me that this isn't the way it was done way-back-when?  When peoples livelihood actually depended on selling those wares?  I personally don't have a problem with it at all, if nothing else it gives me something to read while I'm selling and looking for things to buy, and every once in a while I do find a really good buy from it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/upigboyph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PigboyPH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1256<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/2/02 11:45:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1495.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hungry...</span><hr size=1> Paragraphs are your fr